{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e448c05b-0587-414d-a139-03baae45a2e3","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types from files listed *before* them. Currently `Services.fs` is listed first but depends on `Domain.fs`, which comes second.\n\nFix: reorder so `Domain.fs` comes before `Services.fs`.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_vTcTTNqBTty2f2Yy0MmPLf","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-807862f9cae84d9e8adae6b68faf6536/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-807862f9cae84d9e8adae6b68faf6536/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"a6227e04-b2b2-4a0a-a1a2-e5381d8721a9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference types/modules defined in files that appear *before* them in the compilation order. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n1. `Services.fs` (listed first) — depends on `BrokenOrder.Domain`\n2. `Domain.fs` (listed second) — defines the types\n3. `Program.fs` (listed third) — depends on both\n\n`Services.fs` opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, but `Domain.fs` comes after it in the compile order. The fix is to put `Domain.fs` first, then `Services.fs`, then `Program.fs`.","outputTokens":461,"requestId":"DBE4:192B19:1586606:181C5AC:69FD3403"},"id":"a54aa3f3-b8f9-45ac-a87f-7024915584fd","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:53:34.341Z","parentId":"e0a28b32-92c6-4d5b-9a41-10a575e8e5f1"}
